    <p> Today the day has come that we've been dreading for quite some time. Steffi has to fly back home. We still had a lot on our to-do list, and we wanted to enjoy our remaining time together. </p>
    <p> First, we decided to sort through Steffi's belongings together. So we emptied Hugo, searching for all the individual items for Steffi's suitcases and things I wanted to send home with her. We also took the opportunity to take some decent photos of Hugo for the eventual sale of the vehicle. Then we decided to jump in the pool for a bit and enjoy the warm temperatures. </p>
    <p> After drying off and packing everything else into her suitcases, we decided to eat somewhere before driving to the airport. We ended up at a Greek restaurant and ordered meat dishes. Unfortunately, we only got meat without any side dishes. When Steffi's plate arrived, all I heard was: </p>
    <div class="tag-box tag-box-v2">
      <p> "But I'm hungry!" </p>
